flowRoot.flowPara: Python code is structured on multiple levels.
Each structural level is fully optional.
Callable sub-program with clearly defined input and output.
Bundles data (attributes) and or functionality (methods) to one logical unit. Defined with class
Exists at runtime as a Singleton.
A folder containing at least one module. May contain __init__.py . Used with import
Below 100 lines of code no structure is needed
up to 500 lines can be structured with simple functions
up to 1000 lines can be split into modules
with 10000+ lines there should be a clear package structure
